  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "q8zkd7DDuLlYAtl7vUrgnKyMnx4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nThe Swarm channel's `ConnectionState` is a direct projection of Bee node health probes.\n\n## Mapping (from source)\n| Bee Status | Channel State |\n|---|---|\n| `/health` returns 200 | `connected` |\n| `/health` fails | `reconnecting` |\n| Multiple failures | `error` |\n| Bee URL changed | `connecting` |\n| Channel shutdown | `disconnected` |\n\n## Why this is useful\n- UI components subscribing to `onConnectionStateChange` can render status without custom Bee-health logic.\n- Push is gated on `connected`; in `error` state, operations accumulate in PGlite safely.\n- Reconnect flow (`error \u2192 connected`) triggers catch-up push automatically.\n\n## Source\nSwarm Channel Architecture, \"Connection State\" table; `adapter/src/channel/swarm-channel.ts`.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
    }
  },
